cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.AL, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with communication and computation in a distributed setting.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents solutions for routing and sorting problems.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper considers communication between nodes in a network.
- cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper analyzes the complexity of the presented solutions.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper considers the amount of information that can be exchanged between nodes.
